1
00:00:01,620 --> 00:00:05,670
Episode 19

2
00:00:06,830 --> 00:00:08,500
Did you really run all the way here?

3
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:12,750
I said I'd come riding my bicycle and in the middle of the way I switched to walking.

4
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:16,400
But I thought I was going to die.  You can't do this in summer.

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,690
Of course not.

6
00:00:18,690 --> 00:00:21,630
Thank goodness you didn't get wiped out.

7
00:00:34,030 --> 00:00:41,010
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

8
00:00:44,990 --> 00:00:48,880
Jang Yun, what are you doing here? Weren't you at the hospital?

9
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,350
Insomnia

10
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:52,630
I was released today.

11
00:00:52,630 --> 00:00:57,990
I was worried. But I'm glad to see that you are well. Did you two plan to meet each other?

12
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,360
No.

13
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:03,540
I live there.

14
00:01:03,540 --> 00:01:07,920
Oh, is that so? I didn't know you two lived so close to each other.

15
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:10,770
Yes, somehow it happened.

16
00:01:10,770 --> 00:01:14,470
Of course, I imposed on Yi Yeong many times.

17
00:01:14,470 --> 00:01:19,580
Yes, be that as it may. May I request that you forget you saw us today?

18
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:25,480
I came here without her permission. If strange rumors spread, I will feel sorry to her.

19
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:27,500
So, I request that.

20
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:31,980
Are we going somewhere?

21
00:01:31,980 --> 00:01:35,390
To eat. You didn't eat yet, did you?

22
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:59,450
Why did he come to see me suddenly?

23
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:05,220
You're really not eating.

24
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,800
I'm not in the mood to eat right now.

25
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:15,890
But Conductor, didn't you come here for exercise?

26
00:02:15,890 --> 00:02:17,830
Right?

27
00:02:17,830 --> 00:02:22,920
But seeing you made me hungry. I think my stomach reacted to you.

28
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:34,150
You're wondering why I came here suddenly, aren't you?

29
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:39,120
No, well, not just that...

30
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:41,260
You forgot it all, didn't you?

31
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:44,470
That I said i liked you in front of all the orchestra members?

32
00:02:46,770 --> 00:02:49,230
You forgot.

33
00:02:50,830 --> 00:02:52,830
No, it's not that...

34
00:02:52,830 --> 00:02:54,560
It's not?

35
00:02:55,460 --> 00:02:59,050
It's not that I forgot, Conductor.

36
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:05,360
Someone likes me.

37
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,350
Jang Yun?

38
00:03:10,070 --> 00:03:14,640
It's written on your face that I am correct, and I already had an inkling.

39
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:18,610
Frankly, I don't care much, whether you like someone or not.

40
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:22,560
You don't care?

41
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:30,190
I'm not expecting anything of you. I just intend to make some effort.

42
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:34,310
So at least let me do that. That's all I need.

43
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:36,570
I came to tell you that.

44
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:43,540
What time should I come to pick you up? And what does your Auntie like?

45
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:23,140
It's warm, so why are you outside, and not going in?

46
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:25,360
I wanted to see you come home.

47
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:30,430
Did you enjoy your meal?

48
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,040
Yes.

49
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:41,430
Well, I'm glad you're home. You must be tired, so go in and rest.

50
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:46,450
The wound...

51
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:53,990
What happened to your wound? You shouldn't have left the hospital yet.

52
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,830
I got permission from the doctor.

53
00:05:03,290 --> 00:05:05,990
Don't make me worry, please.

54
00:05:06,770 --> 00:05:10,080
You disappeared without a word, and you don't respond to my texts or answer calls.

55
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:13,750
I imagined all the worst things possible.

56
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:16,830
I'm sorry.

57
00:05:19,410 --> 00:05:22,310
What did you do all day long, anyway?

58
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:34,330
I went to the police station.

59
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:38,420
The station that handled my accident last year.

60
00:05:39,020 --> 00:05:40,740
Police

61
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:44,540
station? Why?

62
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:47,050
I went to turn myself in.

63
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:48,380
What did you say?

64
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:52,320
Really? You went there? What did you say?

65
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:59,050
I told them that I stabbed Kim Ian. But they didn't believe me.

66
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:03,180
They said the case is closed, and they asked me to not come back.

67
00:06:03,180 --> 00:06:05,750
Of course, it's an accident where the criminal confessed.

68
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:08,970
Why would the police open a case that was already closed?

69
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:16,650
What were you thinking? Did you want to go to prison?

70
00:06:16,650 --> 00:06:19,240
I wanted to do something.

71
00:06:20,990 --> 00:06:24,890
I was having a hard time because you were hurt,

72
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:29,190
and to think that it was because of me was even more difficult.

73
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:33,230
When you confessed to me at the hospital,

74
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:36,530
I was so thankful and happy.

75
00:06:38,260 --> 00:06:41,210
Because they were words that I was waiting to hear.

76
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,560
But,

77
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,610
Kim Ian

78
00:06:47,610 --> 00:06:49,930
Seeing the photo of the two of you,

79
00:06:49,930 --> 00:06:51,090
I'm sorry I couldn't answer your phone call that day... I'm sorry I am alive without you...

80
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:54,880
I don't have any right to like you, Yun.

81
00:06:56,470 --> 00:07:00,420
Until I know how Kim Ian died,

82
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,410
I can't accept your feelings, Yun.

83
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:12,210
Whenever you see me, you will think of your brother,

84
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:14,690
And whenever I see you

85
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:20,130
I will be reminded of Kim Ian, your dead brother.

86
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:43,310
♫ Because I can't forget, I cry. ♫

87
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:45,410
Stop it.

88
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:51,510
You don't have to say any more.

89
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:56,650
♫ Why am I still looking for you here? ♫

90
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:59,730
♫ While I'm looking for you who won't come ♫

91
00:07:59,730 --> 00:08:02,330
♫ So I try ♫

92
00:08:02,330 --> 00:08:06,100
♫ You and I ♫

93
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,280
♫ On a day without you, ♫

94
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,730
I'll go in.
♫ I also am not there ♫

95
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:14,100
♫ I know also that you are someone I can't forget ♫

96
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:17,990
♫ Tell me what you doin’ now, even If it is a lie tell me ♫

97
00:08:17,990 --> 00:08:21,250
♫ Tell me everything can go back ♫

98
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:24,930
♫ Even it is a brief moment,  ♫

99
00:08:24,930 --> 00:08:28,550
♫  if I can only call out to you ♫

100
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:32,100
♫ I found myself but I’m still losing myself ♫

101
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:35,440
♫ Can you come back to me? ♫

102
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:40,830
♫ Because I can't forget, I cry. ♫

103
00:08:42,490 --> 00:08:48,080
♫ Even if it is a lie, I try ♫

104
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:11,000
A year ago,  I saw something on the day Kim Ian died.

105
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:15,090
Hong Yi Yeong couldn't get into a car either, so she caught a taxi.

106
00:09:15,090 --> 00:09:18,250
Kim Ian pulled  in front of her taxi.

107
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,210
And?

108
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:22,150
Hong Yi Yeong got in that car.

109
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:27,890
And another car followed the two of them.

110
00:09:27,890 --> 00:09:30,090
A second car?

111
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:32,420
Nam Ju Wan's car.

112
00:09:39,310 --> 00:09:41,880
Jang Yun, what are you doing here?

113
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:44,360
Weren't you at the hospital?

114
00:09:56,390 --> 00:10:02,680
I Wanna Hear Your Song

115
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,030
Good morning. I will be picking you up at 11 a.m.

116
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:39,390
Hello. I'm not late by even one second.

117
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,990
I didn't sleep.

118
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:09,120
You have gotten so good at repotting now.

119
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,670
This kind of work is a piece of cake now.

120
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:15,320
Didn't you say that you have guests?

121
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:18,890
Yes, it's an important guest, so I'd better leave the rest to you, Yeong Gil,

122
00:11:18,890 --> 00:11:20,140
and get going.

123
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:24,190
I'm going to water this.  After all the water runs out, then I will deliver it, rignt?

124
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:26,170
Yes, correct. I entrust you with it.

125
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:29,150
Yes, don't worry and be on your way.

126
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,140
Have a good trip.

127
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:46,460
What smell is this?

128
00:11:46,460 --> 00:11:48,430
Oh, this mortal enemy of mine.

129
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:55,240
I told her to watch this.

130
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,090
What did you burn?

131
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,970
My heart is burnt.

132
00:11:57,970 --> 00:12:00,810
Get up. Won't you get up?

133
00:12:00,810 --> 00:12:02,030
Won't you get up? Won't you get up?

134
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:04,510
What are you doing? I worked late last night.

135
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:06,900
You like to work overtime. Curled up like a 60 year old and sleeping like a dog.

136
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:08,050
Am I a fly to be swatted?

137
00:12:08,050 --> 00:12:10,010
A 60-year-old? Who do you take me for?

138
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:12,850
So are you a youth? You're so old and you can't even date anyone.

139
00:12:12,850 --> 00:12:15,460
It's not that I can't, it's that I won't. Is that a sin?

140
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:17,120
It is a sin.

141
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:21,830
You're over 30, why are you always at home, you parasite?

142
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:25,590
I'm home.
(She gives an honorific ending as a hint there's someone of higher status there)

143
00:12:30,690 --> 00:12:33,350
You're here? Aigoo,

144
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:35,640
there was a fly.

145
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,820
Go in.

146
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:40,350
Honey, the Conductor is here.

147
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:41,970
Come in.

148
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:47,510
What a lively home. I feel like I'm visiting my grandmother.

149
00:12:47,510 --> 00:12:51,860
The thing to pay most attention to this month seems to be here.
C.E.O. Jang Seok Hyeon

150
00:12:51,860 --> 00:12:53,770
Yes, I understand.

151
00:12:54,820 --> 00:12:58,130
You can't  see him without an appointment.

152
00:12:58,130 --> 00:13:00,450
I can sit here, can't I?

153
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:11,000
With all due respect, I can postpone the meeting. I can do so for fifteen minutes.

154
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,710
What's going on?

155
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:24,280
Why did you meet Yun Yeong Gil?

156
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,870
I heard that you hit that punk.

157
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:28,920
He brought photos of you and him, and even a medical report.

158
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:31,880
He said he will tell the media everything he knows and heard.

159
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:35,140
If you were me, could you ignore that?

160
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:41,320
What does that punk know? Did he tell you, Father?

161
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:45,520
Are you investigating me?

162
00:13:46,630 --> 00:13:51,680
Don't act up when you don't know anything. That's why you go around getting hit by people you don't know.

163
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:54,530
Are you worrying about me right now?

164
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:57,860
If you're so worried, why didn't you do it yourself?

165
00:13:57,860 --> 00:14:03,410
You have the ability to find out much easily than I could. Why didn't you do anything?

166
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:07,730
Let me ask you one thing.

167
00:14:07,730 --> 00:14:11,550
What kind of son is Ian to you?

168
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:14,430
Did you really love him?

169
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:21,600
Are you being like this because of that rumor?

170
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:26,690
That Ian wasn't my son, and that I killed him out of revenge against your mother?

171
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:28,550
I don't believe in rumors.

172
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:30,670
I just want to hear the response from my father's mouth, that's all.

173
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:33,910
It's not worth responding to. I refuse.

174
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:38,690
Let me ask you one thing now. Are you alright?

175
00:14:38,690 --> 00:14:39,830
What do you mean?

176
00:14:39,830 --> 00:14:42,680
Are you alright living as Jang Yun?

177
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:46,260
Everyone is calling you by your dead brother's name.

178
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:49,430
Doesn't it hurt you,

179
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,680
to live like a ghost?

180
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:58,700
No matter how much your blood boils, once someone is dead, he is dead.

181
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:02,570
The living must move on from that death.

182
00:15:02,570 --> 00:15:05,480
I am doing this in order to be able to move on.

183
00:15:10,890 --> 00:15:13,770
I heard that you will be joining our board of directors.

184
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:18,680
Out of so many orchestras, why Sinyeong Philharmonic? To push me out?

185
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,680
Or do you have another purpose?

186
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:24,870
Because I didn't like you living like a ghost, wrapped up in Ian.

187
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:30,790
Is it wrong for a father to show concern for his child?

188
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:35,640
It's dismaying to hear such words from you, Father.

189
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:41,620
If you wanted to act like a father, why didn't you do it when Ian died unfairly?

190
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:46,870
You can join Sinyeong Philharmonic, but you can't remove me so easily.

191
00:15:46,870 --> 00:15:51,740
Until I find out who killed Ian and why, I will never leave Sinyeong Philharmonic.

192
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:54,640
You suspect it, too, don't you, Father?

193
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:59,750
That the person who killed Ian may be there?

194
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:13,710
Do it faster.

195
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:18,610
Your rhythm is so good.

196
00:16:18,610 --> 00:16:21,400
Where do you think Yi Yeong gets her talent?

197
00:16:22,620 --> 00:16:26,230
They like each other so much. It's as if they met before.

198
00:16:26,230 --> 00:16:29,960
I know, right? It's so nice to see Uncle smile.

199
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:33,970
Without your physical abuse, this would be heaven.

200
00:16:33,970 --> 00:16:36,600
Go in. Go in.

201
00:16:37,550 --> 00:16:40,430
I don't know why she acts like that, who does she take after?

202
00:16:41,570 --> 00:16:42,690
Oh, he's already here?

203
00:16:42,690 --> 00:16:44,170
Hey, can you open the door?

204
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,820
It's probably the part-time worker from the flower shop.

205
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:48,390
Yes.

206
00:16:50,630 --> 00:16:53,020
I'm coming.

207
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:56,990
Please come in.

208
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,960
Hold on...

209
00:17:08,950 --> 00:17:10,840
Hello.

210
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:15,620
Auntie?

211
00:17:15,620 --> 00:17:18,990
Hold on, Yeong Gil. I'm almost done packing it.

212
00:17:18,990 --> 00:17:20,680
Yes.

213
00:17:37,630 --> 00:17:39,250
My first time meeting you, Owner.

214
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:43,760
Yes, Yeong Gil, my wife is always praising how well you work.

215
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,810
Oh, how grateful I am.

216
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:51,040
I wanted to give you some side dishes. You could eat this for a few meals.

217
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:53,170
So much? Thank you.

218
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:54,370
You can go home for today.

219
00:17:54,370 --> 00:17:55,980
Yes, I will enjoy this.

220
00:17:55,980 --> 00:17:57,930
Thank you.

221
00:17:57,930 --> 00:17:59,720
I am fine.

222
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:02,020
I'll be going now.

223
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:15,380
Assemblyman.  It's the people pushing for amendment of the private school law.

224
00:18:15,380 --> 00:18:18,090
Of course, I saw that weekly magazine.

225
00:18:18,090 --> 00:18:21,220
Does that make any sense? It's saying that we haven't been audited for 35 years.

226
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:23,930
We spend several hundred million wons a year so that we can be audited.

227
00:18:23,930 --> 00:18:26,170
Yes, I will contact you soon.

228
00:18:26,170 --> 00:18:27,820
Yes.

229
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:30,920
These dirty bastards, aigoo.

230
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:34,280
I guess they ran out of money.

231
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,630
These rotten jerks.

232
00:18:38,870 --> 00:18:41,010
You shocked me.

233
00:18:41,010 --> 00:18:42,850
What now?

234
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:45,000
My heart.

235
00:18:57,220 --> 00:18:59,800
What is this?

236
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,690
Don't you want money?

237
00:19:01,690 --> 00:19:03,840
But it's too little.

238
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:08,220
- Too little?
- Look here, Professor.

239
00:19:08,220 --> 00:19:12,720
There are so many people involved in that incident from a year ago, many more than I thought.

240
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:15,820
You're always at the school, so you don't seem to know.

241
00:19:15,820 --> 00:19:19,800
With just a small mistake, you could be the one who gets destroyed.

242
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:24,600
This bastard, really... Are you bluffing me?

243
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:27,790
It's not a bluff, but advice.

244
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:30,670
It's already been a year since the accident.

245
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:34,790
But if you haven't "updated," what will you do?

246
00:19:36,470 --> 00:19:38,580
What are you saying?

247
00:19:39,370 --> 00:19:41,760
What do you mean?!?

248
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,490
Do you know who Jang Yun's father is?

249
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:47,230
Who is he?

250
00:19:47,230 --> 00:19:51,710
The newly appointed member of Sinyeong Philharmonic's Board of Directors.

251
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,990
What?

252
00:20:12,790 --> 00:20:15,560
I was surprised to hear from you.

253
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:19,520
Didn't you refuse me that day?

254
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:22,350
I said to lay off when you broached the topic of my son.

255
00:20:22,350 --> 00:20:25,700
If you provoke him, he can be relentless.

256
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:29,000
I remembered what you said to me, that is why I contacted you.

257
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,320
What was that?

258
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:36,200
I looked into your performances, Eun Ju. I like it.

259
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:39,100
I don't have untrained ears.

260
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:42,940
Everyone in the family except me is a musician.

261
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:45,660
You must need a stage.

262
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,630
How about a change, with me?

263
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,300
What do you need?

264
00:20:54,300 --> 00:21:00,900
I want you to tell me what you did with Professor Kang Myeong Seok of Sinyeong Music College. And what you know about him.

265
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:03,430
And everything else you know about him.

266
00:21:03,430 --> 00:21:05,200
Professor Kang?

267
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:09,100
Why do you want to know that?

268
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:15,010
Eun Ju, is it your dream to continue to play with Sinyeong Philharmonic?

269
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:19,990
That was true before, but not anymore.

270
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:25,700
So you won't mind if Sinyeong Philharmonic  is discarded, right?

271
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:36,680
More than that, I hope we can change the conductor.

272
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:42,390
The conductor? What do you mean?

273
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:45,300
Just as I said.

274
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:47,960
Please fire Nam Ju Wan so that I don't have to see him.

275
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:51,370
Then I will give you what you want.

276
00:21:57,560 --> 00:22:02,470
The Chairman of the Board and C.E.O. Jang of Nano Semi-Conductor, how long have they known each other?

277
00:22:02,470 --> 00:22:04,900
I think since last autumn?

278
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:07,680
They met by chance by sitting on adjacent seats at the opera, I was told.

279
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:09,640
By chance?

280
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:15,940
Did you know that the guest member of the orchestra is C.E.O. Jang's son?

281
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:18,460
Jang Yun? Is that true?

282
00:22:18,460 --> 00:22:22,240
Are you aware this can be a problem? The media can attack us for this.

283
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:25,460
Remove C.E.O. Jang from the board. I can't agree to this.

284
00:22:25,460 --> 00:22:27,380
How can you say that now?

285
00:22:27,380 --> 00:22:29,950
Tomorrow is the Encouragement Night ceremony. We already sent out the invitations.

286
00:22:29,950 --> 00:22:33,100
Then call everyone politely and cancel it.

287
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:37,240
I can't do that.

288
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,060
What right do you have, Professor?

289
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:43,490
What about the Chairwoman of the Board? Isn't this an abuse of authority?

290
00:22:46,780 --> 00:22:48,650
Did you say abuse of authority?

291
00:22:48,650 --> 00:22:52,960
If I want to cause a problem, I can even get rid of the Chairwoman.

292
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:55,450
After all, she is just a face for publicity.

293
00:22:55,450 --> 00:22:59,990
Without C.E.O. Jang's money, we can't even hold the 20th-anniversary concert.

294
00:22:59,990 --> 00:23:01,690
Why are you doing this, anyway?

295
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:05,410
Does he know some weakness of yours he can threaten you with?

296
00:23:09,510 --> 00:23:11,190
I can't believe my ears.

297
00:23:11,190 --> 00:23:13,400
Think it over well,

298
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,940
if you don't want Sinyeong Philharmonic to shut down.

299
00:23:15,940 --> 00:23:19,420
This is a world where even politicians all get cast out because of their children.

300
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:20,820
Do you want to get involved in such a thing?

301
00:23:20,820 --> 00:23:23,730
The Art Foundation has been in deficit for five years, hasn't it?

302
00:23:23,730 --> 00:23:28,470
But it still operates. And you don't realize who's behind that?

303
00:23:28,470 --> 00:23:31,760
Please use this.

304
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:34,430
Please. This.

305
00:23:42,310 --> 00:23:46,760
Assistant Yang, Maestro Nam requested Jang Yun's résumé last time, didn't he?

306
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:49,110
He didn't tell you why?

307
00:23:50,850 --> 00:23:52,780
It's nothing.

308
00:24:03,330 --> 00:24:05,380
Maestro Nam

309
00:24:06,130 --> 00:24:09,680
Yes, it's me. Let's meet today.

310
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,980
This isn't something I can tell you on the phone.

311
00:24:15,630 --> 00:24:18,790
I wanted to hang out  with you until late, but sorry.

312
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:22,530
But if you really want to, call me. I will come.

313
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:26,470
By the way, Ms. Bok Bun said she is coming.

314
00:24:26,470 --> 00:24:27,400
When?

315
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:31,400
A day before the performance. It's the first time since I became a conductor.

316
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:38,200
I always visited her, but she never came before. You know, she's pretty tough.

317
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:40,140
I'm sure she feels differently this time.

318
00:24:40,140 --> 00:24:42,570
It's your first time after you were appointed.

319
00:24:42,570 --> 00:24:44,600
And I want to do well, because of that.

320
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:47,450
I'm afraid of disappointing the goddess.

321
00:24:54,690 --> 00:24:56,800
I'm glad you're there.

322
00:24:56,800 --> 00:25:00,250
When Grandma comes, she will feel comfortable.

323
00:25:00,250 --> 00:25:02,880
It's warm. You should go in.

324
00:25:05,260 --> 00:25:07,360
Have a safe trip home.

325
00:25:36,340 --> 00:25:38,260
Wait for a bit, Yeong Gil.

326
00:25:38,260 --> 00:25:40,160
Yes.

327
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,890
Wow, I was shocked.

328
00:25:56,890 --> 00:25:59,230
Did you come to practice?

329
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:10,420
You know who this belongs to, don't you?

330
00:26:16,030 --> 00:26:18,380
Whose is it?

331
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:22,560
A years ago did you collaborate with Kim Ian? When he played with the Asia Philharmonic?

332
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:24,570
I did.

333
00:26:24,570 --> 00:26:27,410
Did you see him after the concert?

334
00:26:27,410 --> 00:26:32,850
How do you know Kim Ian? Isn't that what you should tell me first?

335
00:26:33,750 --> 00:26:36,700
You followed Ian by car that day, didn't you?

336
00:26:40,490 --> 00:26:44,080
Who told you that? Eun Ju?

337
00:26:45,630 --> 00:26:48,520
Did you kill Ian, Conductor?

338
00:26:50,750 --> 00:26:55,550
Did you kill Ian, I asked you.

339
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:59,740
Are you asking me now if I killed someone?

340
00:26:59,740 --> 00:27:02,040
Why would I kill Kim Ian, I don't have any reason to.

341
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:05,190
You may have had one.

342
00:27:06,670 --> 00:27:11,990
Why do you keep bothering Hong Yi Yeong? Is that related to Ian as well?

343
00:27:11,990 --> 00:27:14,090
Why are you curious about that?

344
00:27:14,090 --> 00:27:18,800
Are you afraid that I approached her on purpose, or that my feelings might be real?

345
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:21,240
Shall I take a guess?

346
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:26,810
You know very well that Hong Yi Yeong was Kim Ian's assistant.

347
00:27:26,810 --> 00:27:31,020
And you already know that those two were together that day, a year ago.

348
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:34,030
And that Hong Yi Yeong, after that accident,

349
00:27:34,030 --> 00:27:38,570
lost all her memories. I'm sure you know that, too.

350
00:27:38,570 --> 00:27:41,880
Perhaps you're afraid that Hong Yi Yeong will remember what happened that day,

351
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:45,800
and because you're afraid of that, that is why you're keeping her close?

352
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:51,590
What will you do if she remembers? Will you kill her?

353
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:57,460
Jang Yun, are you writing a novel?

354
00:27:57,460 --> 00:28:00,560
Why would I kill Hong Yi Yeong?

355
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:03,590
Do you really hate it so much that I'm seeing Yi Yeong?

356
00:28:03,590 --> 00:28:07,590
If that is the case, just say it. I could at least understand that.

357
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:13,820
Why are you accusing someone of murder without any evidence?

358
00:28:13,820 --> 00:28:18,640
And what's with this knife?

359
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:22,110
Can you really threaten your conductor like this?

360
00:28:29,780 --> 00:28:33,050
Do you really not remember this knife?

361
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:35,510
It's the knife that Ian was stabbed with.

362
00:28:36,220 --> 00:28:39,830
Let's say this is the knife Kim Ian was stabbed with.

363
00:28:39,830 --> 00:28:43,440
Then why are you giving such an important piece of evidence to me?

364
00:28:45,860 --> 00:28:48,790
So that you will think it over carefully.

365
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:55,000
Whether this knife really is in your memories, or you really never saw it before.

366
00:29:34,170 --> 00:29:36,550
Sorry for calling you so late.

367
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:43,320
About Jang Yun being hired a guest performer,

368
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:46,530
is there some reason I am not aware of, perhaps?

369
00:29:46,530 --> 00:29:52,040
The reason is which reason?  Because Eun Ju said she's against it? Why Jang Yun out of the blue?

370
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:54,770
Professor Kang is acting sensitive about it.

371
00:29:54,770 --> 00:29:57,900
Is Professor Kang creating a fuss about his appointment?

372
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:02,500
It's not that. A new member is joining our board of directors.

373
00:30:02,500 --> 00:30:06,470
I don't know what it is, but it seems that person has a weakness to hold over Professor Kang.

374
00:30:06,470 --> 00:30:08,670
So he is jumping up and down, throwing fits.

375
00:30:08,670 --> 00:30:12,950
He says if we don't push him out of the board, he will shut down Sinyeong Philharmonic.

376
00:30:12,950 --> 00:30:14,870
How is that person related to Jang Yun?

377
00:30:14,870 --> 00:30:17,930
Jang Yun is his son, I hear.

378
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:23,420
Son? What does that man do?

379
00:30:24,130 --> 00:30:27,640
He's the CEO of just a mid-sized company. His name is Jang Seok Hyeon.

380
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:31,970
I'm worried that Professor Kang will make up a story which isn't true.

381
00:30:31,970 --> 00:30:35,590
He's been sensitive recently. He made the request.

382
00:30:35,590 --> 00:30:39,930
I thought that you invited him here because you knew. You were the one who brought Jang Yun here.

383
00:30:39,930 --> 00:30:43,550
Why, did you think I got paid for it or something?

384
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:47,100
I know that you wouldn't, but someone could accuse you of that.

385
00:30:47,100 --> 00:30:49,510
Professor Kang is like a snake, as you know.

386
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:52,060
Anyway, I thought you should know.
